        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer46601009" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4876305568339284119">I finished this book in December of &apos;07, Johnny Got his Gun, and it made me want to shoot myself in the face.<br/>It is written in second person limited, which is annoying enough if not for the added limitation of narrating through a character with no eyes, nose, ears, mouth or limbs. Written primarily in stream-of-consciousness, I simply wanted to cut my eyes out so that I could at least fall asleep on my 5-hour flight. Johnny was supposed to be an anti-war novel, receiving a mountain of praise for </span>
  <span id="freeText4876305568339284119" style="display:none">I finished this book in December of '07, Johnny Got his Gun, and it made me want to shoot myself in the face.<br />It is written in second person limited, which is annoying enough if not for the added limitation of narrating through a character with no eyes, nose, ears, mouth or limbs. Written primarily in stream-of-consciousness, I simply wanted to cut my eyes out so that I could at least fall asleep on my 5-hour flight. Johnny was supposed to be an anti-war novel, receiving a mountain of praise for being eloquent and emotional. It sure did drive me to emotion - uncontrollable masochism.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4876305568339284119" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
